JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Aim-listed Bluejay Mining has established Dundas Titanium, a Greenlandic domiciled subsidiary, to operate its Pituffik titanium project, in Greenland. &ldquo;The subsidiary was created to facilitate the permitting process, which will culminate in the lodging of the exploitation application later in 2017,&rdquo; the company said in a statement. Bluejay is now focused on starting production at Pituffik, a high-grade mineral sand ilmenite project, in 2018. It recently applied for the Pituffik licence to be transferred to Dundas and expects the process to be completed in the coming months.&nbsp; Bluejay COO Hans Jenson will also be the MD for Dundas.